# Mince – AI Agent Rules
# Copyright © 2025 Meverik Studio®

## Project Overview
Czech-language numismatic coin collection web app.
Stack: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + MUI v5 + Supabase + Vercel.

## Key Conventions

### Language
- UI text, comments, and variable names are in Czech
- Code logic identifiers (functions, types) use English
- Error messages may be in Czech for end users

### File Structure
- Active source: `frontend/src/`
- Do NOT touch `_archive/` — historical only
- Services go in `frontend/src/services/coinService.ts`
- Types go in `frontend/src/types/coin.ts`
- Pages go in `frontend/src/pages/`
- Shared components go in `frontend/src/components/`

### Styling & Theme
- Use MUI v5 `sx` prop for all styling (no separate CSS files unless necessary)
- Dark glassmorphism theme — background `#070b12`, cards with `rgba(255,255,255,0.04)` bg
- Primary accent: gold `#d4a847` | Secondary: purple `#7c4dff`
- Border radius: 12–16px for cards, 8px for buttons
- All cards use `backdropFilter: 'blur(12px)'` and subtle border `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)`
- Font: Inter (loaded via index.html)

### Data Fetching
- Use TanStack React Query for all server state
- Query key pattern: `['coins', filters]`, `['coin', id]`, `['collections']`, `['coin-stats']`
- Mutations invalidate related queries on success

### Forms
- Use React Hook Form for all form state
- Validation inline with `rules` prop

### Supabase
- Client in `frontend/src/lib/supabase.ts` — import `{ supabase }` from there
- Never hardcode credentials — use env vars `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` and `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
- Images go to bucket `coin-images` in Supabase Storage

### TypeScript
- Always type function parameters and return values
- Use `interface` for object shapes (not `type` aliases for objects)
- Prefer `const` over `let`

### Copyright
- Include `© Meverik Studio®` in app footer
- Do not remove existing copyright notices

## What NOT to Do
- Do not add new dependencies without checking for existing alternatives
- Do not modify `supabase/migrations/` without understanding the full schema impact
- Do not commit `.env` files — use `.env.example` as the template
- Do not use `any` TypeScript type — prefer `unknown` if type is truly dynamic
- Do not write CSS files unless MUI sx prop is insufficient
